{{wikipedia}}

==English==

===Etymology===
Old English [[æl|ǣl]].

===Pronunciation===
*ēl, /iːl/, /<tt>I:l</tt>/

===Noun===
{{en-noun-reg}}

# Any [[fish]] of the order [[Anguilliformes]] which are elongated and resemble [[snake]]s. There are freshwater and marine species.

====Derived terms====
* [[eelpout]], [[eel-pout]]
* [[conger eel]]
* [[electric eel]]
* [[glass eel]]
* [[moray eel]]
* [[sand eel]]

====See also====
* [[elver]]

